ssttp.arrangement.direct-debit.form.guarantee.title=Direct Debit Guarantee
ssttp.arrangement.direct-debit.form.guarantee.list.1=This Guarantee is offered by all banks and building societies that accept instructions to pay Direct Debits.
ssttp.arrangement.direct-debit.form.guarantee.list.2=I there are any changes to the amount, date or frequency of your Direct Debit HM Revenue & Customs (HMRC) will notify you 10 working days in advance of your account being debited or as otherwise agreed. If you request HMRC to collect a payment, confirmation of the amount and date will be given to you at the time of the request.
ssttp.arrangement.direct-debit.form.guarantee.list.3=If an error is made in the payment of your Direct Debit, by HMRC or your bank or building society, you are entitled to a full immediate refund of the amount paid from your bank or building society.
ssttp.arrangement.direct-debit.form.guarantee.list.4=If you receive a refund you are not entitled to, you must pay it back when HMRC asks you to.
ssttp.arrangement.direct-debit.form.guarantee.list.5=You can cancel a Direct Debit at any time by simply contacting your bank or building society. Written confirmation may be required. Please notify us.


